text: Kendall Katwalk is a 150 yard long narrow pathway blasted out of a steeply sloped granite rock face on the north ridge of Kendall Peak approximately 6 miles northeast of Snoqualmie Pass. It is a segment of Section J of Pacific Crest Trail and the construction was completed in 1979. It is a popular destination for day hikers, trail runners, and backpackers. ==References== ==External links== * Washington Trail Association - Hiking guide - Kendall Katwalk Category:Landforms of Kittitas County, Washington Category:Hiking trails in Washington (state)
